# AAF Â· API Contract Rule (MANDATORY)

## Versioning

- All routes live under `/api/v1/`. Breaking changes go to `/api/v2/` â€” never mutate `/v1`.
- Health endpoints (`/api/v1/health`, `/api/v1/health/ready`) are the only unauthenticated ones.

## Routers

- One router per resource: `backend/api/routers/<resource>.py`.
- `APIRouter(prefix="/<resource>", tags=["<resource>"])`.
- Every new router must be registered in `backend/api/__init__.py`.

## Schemas

- Request schema: `<ResourceAction>Request`. Response schema: `<ResourceAction>Response`.
- Located in `backend/api/schemas/<resource>.py`.
- Request models MUST set `model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid")`.
- Never return SQLAlchemy models; always a response schema.
- All datetimes are UTC ISO 8601 with `Z` suffix.

## Async

- Every route handler is `async def`. Long tasks (> 1s) enqueue to ARQ and return 202 + `task_id`. Never block the request thread.

## Errors

- Raise `AAFError` subclasses. The global exception handler converts them to RFC 7807 Problem Details JSON.
- Never return raw dict `{"error": ...}` from a handler.
- Status codes:
  - 400 bad request / 401 unauth / 403 forbidden / 404 not found / 409 conflict / 422 validation
  - 429 rate limited / 500 server error / 502 upstream / 503 busy / 504 timeout

## SSE

- Endpoint pattern: `GET /api/v1/tasks/{id}/stream`.
- Use `sse_starlette.EventSourceResponse`.
- Event schema in `backend/api/schemas/events.py`; each event type has a Pydantic model.
- Heartbeat event `ping` every 15s.
- Close stream on `task.finished | task.error | task.cancelled`.

## OpenAPI

- `summary="..."` on every route (one line, used in the auto-generated Swagger).
- At least one example per response model (`json_schema_extra`).
- Tags match resource names exactly.

## Pagination

- **Cursor-based** only. Request: `?limit=20&cursor=<opaque>`. Response: `{ items, next_cursor }`.
- No page-number pagination anywhere.

## Auth

- Use `Depends(get_current_user)` unless explicitly public.
- Admin actions: `Depends(require_admin)`.
- `AUTH_DISABLED=true` makes `get_current_user` return `User(id="anonymous")` â€” tests rely on this.

## File uploads

- Use `UploadFile` + stream to MinIO via `backend/core/storage/minio_client.py`.
- Max size configurable via `AAF_MAX_UPLOAD_MB` (default 50).

## Rate limits (best effort)

- Per-user / endpoint rate limits via a simple Redis INCR pattern (`backend/api/ratelimit.py`). Not a hard wall â€” just a guard.

## Checklist for every new endpoint

- [ ] Schemas live in `backend/api/schemas/<resource>.py`
- [ ] Router registered in `backend/api/__init__.py`
- [ ] `summary` + at least one OpenAPI example
- [ ] Error paths raise `AAFError`
- [ ] At least one integration test hitting the route
- [ ] If returning a task id, SSE stream subscription works (integration-tested)
